  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    AnalyzeColorMap, GreyColorModel

    public class CNUColorModel
extends IndexColorModel
implements CNUFileObject, iiVScriptable
    CNUColorMap extends IndexColorModel to define some standard tools.

    iiV1.0

      • indexColorModelsEqual

        public static boolean indexColorModelsEqual(IndexColorModel icm1,
                                            IndexColorModel icm2)
        Compares two IndexColorModels for equality. Needed because JDK 1.4 seems to fail testing this equality which sometimes causes problems building scripts. Hope this problem doesn't pop up with IndexColorModels that are not CNUColorModels.
        Parameters:
        icm1 - first index color model to compare to second
        icm2 - second index color model to compare to first
        Returns:
        true if icm1 and icm2 would return all the same values for the same indices.

      • WriteColorMapScript

        public static void WriteColorMapScript(CNUFile cnufile,
                                       Object cd,
                                       IndexColorModel icm)
                                throws IOException
        Writes a color map to a script file.
        Parameters:
        cnufile - CNUFile to write to.
        cd - Determines how to handle write overs if file exists. If cd is null, the file is written over with no warning, else if cd instanceof ContinueDialog, the dialog is used to query the user before writting over, else no write over is performed.
        icm - IndexColorModel to write to file.
        Throws:
        IOException - thrown if error writing to cnufile.
